The paper focuses on analyzing the use of hashtags in social media during the 2019 Lok Sabha elections in India. This involves studying trends, events, latent topics, and semantic similarity of hashtags to relate them to election outcomes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper deals with analyzing social media data. The second likely sub-category is cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) as the paper also deals with political campaigning and community building. The third likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper uses Latent Dirichlet Allocation to find topic patterns in the dataset. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper uses skip-gram word embedding model to find semantically similar hashtags. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) as the paper deals with analyzing data from a cybersecurity perspective.
